250 g Ground Beef
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
1 unit(s) Tomato
1 unit(s) Lime
½ unit(s) Iceberg Lettuce Head
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
0.13 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Peel, then cut onion into 1/2-inch pieces. (TIP: Do you like raw onions on your tacos? Set some aside before cooking the rest with beef in step 2.)
Remove and discard outer layer of iceberg lettuce. Remove stem, cut half the lettuce into thin strips (use all the lettuce for 4 ppl).
Core, then cut tomato into 1/2-inch pieces.
Zest, then juice half the lime. Cut remaining lime into wedges.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add beef to the dry pan. Break beef into smaller pieces.
Add onions. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender and beef is cooked through, 4-5 min.**
Add tomato sauce base and Mexican Seasoning. Stir to combine.
Add 1/3 cup (1/2 cup) water, then bring to a simmer.
Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly, 1-2 min.

Meanwhile, add sour cream, lime zest, 1 tsp (2 tsp) lime juice and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) sugar to a small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Just before serving, wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave until pliable and warmed through, 30 sec-1 min.

Divide tortillas between plates.
Spread lime crema onto tortillas.
Top with beef, tomatoes, lettuce, cheese, and raw onions, if desired.
Squeeze a lime wedge over top, if desired.